The Executive Chairman of Etsako East local government area, Hon. (Mrs) Benedicta Ebuehi, said the recent awards bestowed on Governor Godwin Obaseki was a clear testimony of the governors Sterling performance. The Council boss who was reacting to the honour on the governor told newsmen in Benin City, Edo state that it was a award well deserved. Recalled that Obaseki weekend received the Governor of the year award on Economic and Youth Empowerment by the Daily Independent Newspapers. The award is coming barely two week when Obaseki was decorated as the Extra-ordinary Personality of the year (2019) by the Silver Group in Lagos. Ebuehi, who was part of the Governor’s entourage to the awards ceremony likened Governor Obaseki to a child who has washed his hands clean and therefore qualified to dine with kings. “No one should be surprised that Governor Godwin Obaseki has continued to receive rave reviews from across the length and breadth of Nigeria and even beyond considering his antecedents in the business world where he has been heralded as a world class technocrat,” Hon. Benedicta Ebuehi said. “This mercurial performance made him a sought-after personality by governments which was why when he joined the government, he was not a fringe player but was at the core of the administration preceding his current administration”. “It is therefore not surprising that within three years in office, Obaseki”s economic acumen and administrative competence have continued to receive recognitions from all over the places”.